bug.short_desc: Polyfill methods should be findable using the search

long_desc.thetext: The polyfilled methods are not findable by using the search box. It would be a great help if these methods can be found by e.g. typing 'bind' in the search box like shown at the screenshot.
Same for search terms like "click" or "mouseout" - there are no results. Maybe you can take that also into account.
Event normalization methods should also be documented.

Polyfill and event normalization methods are now fully documented and searchable (with e3abdfd679a6e485ce3b15ef93a919bb033f4574 on master).
Event types aren't listed in the module index currently, so making them searchable is a different task. Nico (or Alex), please feel free to open a new enhancement report for this.
